|}

* The film won an [[Academy Awards|Oscar]] for best [[Academy Award for Writing Original Screenplay|original screenplay]]. It was also nominated for best [[Academy Award for Directing|director]] (the first time an American woman was nominated for this award), [[Academy Award for Best Picture|picture]] and [[Academy Award for Best Actor|actor]].

* The film won [[Golden Globe Award|Golden Globes]] for best [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture - Musical or Comedy|musical or comedy motion picture]], [[Golden Globe Award for Best Screenplay|screenplay]], and [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor - Motion Picture Musical or Comedy#2000s|musical or comedy actor]]. It was also nominated for best [[Golden Globe Award for Best Director - Motion Picture|director]], and [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress - Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|musical or comedy actress]].

* At the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA]] film awards, the film won the best editing, [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|actor]] and [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role#Winners 1968-present|actress]] awards. It was also nominated for best film, director, original screenplay, music and cinematography.

* It won four [[IFP Independent Spirit Awards]], for best feature, director, male lead, and screenplay.
